      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GROOT BALE (2) flew the lids with a slick early split last time and went on to clock 23.26 as a strongly fancied winner over 410m at Horsham. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Will go close again if runs up to latest. PADDY'S WAY (7) is racing well without winning, recording three minors on end, the latest hitting the ground running with a fast early sectional but finishing in the minors again when second (25.78) over 450m at this track. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. GEORGINA ROSE (4) lines up here off a comfortable win at this track after jumping from box 4 (25.58). Has the squeeze box to overcome and will need the breaks early. Won at her only start from this box. Significant danger. INGA NOAH (8) was in the money last start and wasn't beaten far - should feature again.",
